msgid ""
"TimorMart is Timor-Leste's own online marketplace — a place for people across the country\n"
"        to buy and sell directly with each other, without needing a physical shop or a big budget to get started."
msgstr ""
"TimorMart mak merkadu online rasik Timor-Leste — fatin ida ba ema hotu iha rai laran tomak\n"
"        atu sosa no fa'an malu direitamente, la presiza loja fízika ka osan boot atu hahú."

msgid "Why we built this"
msgstr "Tanbasá ami harii ida-ne'e"

msgid ""
"Retail in Timor-Leste is spread across markets, small shops and word-of-mouth —\n"
"            great for community, but hard for a buyer to compare options or for a small seller to reach\n"
"            customers outside their own neighbourhood. TimorMart brings that same everyday buying and selling\n"
"            online: a single, trusted place where anyone can list a product and anyone can find it, whether\n"
"            it's brand new or a good second-hand find."
msgstr ""
"Komérsiu iha Timor-Leste fahe iha merkadu, loja ki'ik no lia-fuan husi ema ba ema —\n"
"            di'ak ba komunidade, maibé susar ba kompradór atu kompara opsaun ka ba vendedór ki'ik atu to'o\n"
"            kliente sira liur husi sira-nia vizinhansa. TimorMart lori hela-fatin komprasaun no fa'an loron-loron ne'e\n"
"            ba online: fatin ida deit, konfiavel, ne'ebé ema hotu bele listu produtu no ema hotu bele hetan,\n"
"            keta produtu foun ka sasán uza-tiha ne'ebé di'ak."

